        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 25 at 6:18PM CDT until May 25 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 618 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Big Spring,
moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
considerable tree damage. Wind damage is also likely to
mobile homes, roofs, and outbuildings.

Locations impacted include...
Big Spring, Luther, Big Spring Country Club, and Big Spring
McMahon-Wrinkle Airpark.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 173 and 184.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

This is a dangerous storm, capable of producing large hail driven by
severe winds! SEEK SHELTER NOW inside a sturdy structure and stay
away from windows! If you are caught outdoors, cover your head and
neck.</instruction>
